  sodium: 1490 mg
time required: 30 minutes
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/red-hot-tomato-soup-5a4e5fdd2c3e0857cb7bd282
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to upper position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Halve, peel, and finely dice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve @lemon{1}. Melt @butter{1%tbsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add onion and half the garlic. Cook, stirring often, until softened, about ~{5%minutes}.

Season onion with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then stir @crushed tomatoes{1%13.76oz can}, 1 1/2 cups water, and @veggie stock concentrate{1} into pot. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and reduce to a simmer. Cook until thickened, about ~{8-10%minutes}. Meanwhile, place @butter{1%tbsp} and remaining garlic in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Heat in microwave until melted, about ~{30%seconds}.

Place @naan bread{4} on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}. Brush or drizzle all over with garlic butter. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Bake in oven until lightly toasted, about ~{4-5%minutes}. Sprinkle naans with @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, then return sheet to oven and continue baking until naans are crisp and mozzarella melts, about ~{3%minutes} more.

Once soup is thickened, set aside off heat and let cool slightly. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in @sugar{1%tsp}, half the @sour cream{3%tbsp}, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%pinch} (to taste). Taste and season again with salt and pepper.

> If soup tastes sharp, add another 1/2 tsp sugar.

Place @mixed greens{2%oz}, @sunflower seeds{1%oz}, @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and a squeeze or two of lemon (to taste) in a #medium bowl{}. Toss to combine. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cut naans in half. Divide soup between #bowls{} and dollop with remaining @sour cream{3%tbsp}. Sprinkle with a pinch of @chili flakes{1%pinch} (to taste). Serve soup with naans and salad to the side.

> Dunk the naans into the soup to get the best of both worlds.